
What is S3?
 
 - Secure, Durable, Highly Scalabe object storge
 - Store objects/Files within AWS
 - Cannot install a DB/OS on it
 - Flat objects/Static files

What is EBS (Elastic Block Store)

 - Persisten block storage volumes
 - Basically a virtual hard disk in the cloud
 - Designed to have OS and DB installed on them
 - Automatically replicated within its availability zone

What is EFS (Elastic File System)

 - File storage for EC2 Instances 
 - No set size, it grows and shrinks automatically (Its Elastic)
 - Attached to EC2 instances
